Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the offense of assault. I admit that I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. I fully take responsibility for my actions and I am deeply remorseful for the harm I have caused.

The incident occurred when my employee made a serious mistake at work, one that would have severe financial consequences for my company. This mistake triggered a surge of anger within me, causing me to act impulsively and without considering the consequences of my actions. However, I recognize that my response was disproportionate and unjustifiable.

Immediately after the incident, I deeply regretted my actions and took immediate steps to rectify the situation. I rushed my employee to the closest emergency room to ensure he received the necessary medical attention and I have offered to cover the expenses incurred for his hospital bills. I understand that this cannot undo the harm caused, but I hope it demonstrates my sincere regret and commitment to making amends.

It is important to note that I am a 40-year-old individual with no prior criminal record. This incident is an aberration in an otherwise law-abiding life. I take pride in maintaining a clean record and have always strived to contribute positively to my community and society at large.

As I reflect upon my actions, it is evident that my anger got the better of me on that particular day. I recognize the need to seek help and work on managing my emotions in a healthier manner. While this does not justify my behavior, it does indicate a willingness to take necessary steps to ensure that such an incident does not occur again.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I stand here today, pleading guilty, fully acknowledging the gravity of my actions. I would like to reiterate my heartfelt remorse and extend my sincerest apologies to the victim and his family. I accept any consequence that the court deems just and fair, and I am committed to working towards personal growth, rehabilitation, and making amends for the harm I have caused.

Thank you for your consideration.

Sincerely,
Aleksander Nowak

